{{nihongo|'''Kyūshū Electric Power Company'''|九州電力株式会社|Kyūshū Denryoku Kabushiki Gaisha}} ({{Tyo|9508}}, [[Osaka Securities Exchange|OSE]]: 9508) is a Japanese energy company that provides power to 7 prefectures ([[Fukuoka Prefecture|Fukuoka]], [[Nagasaki Prefecture|Nagasaki]], [[Ōita Prefecture|Ōita]], [[Saga Prefecture|Saga]], [[Miyazaki Prefecture|Miyazaki]], [[Kumamoto Prefecture|Kumamoto]], [[Kagoshima Prefecture|Kagoshima]]), and recently, to some parts of [[Hiroshima Prefecture]]. Its shortened name of {{nihongo|九電|Kyuu den}} is sometimes used. In 2011 the company was criticised for attempting to manipulate public opinion in favor of reactivating two reactors at the [[Genkai Nuclear Power Plant]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mdn.mainichi.jp/perspectives/news/20110708p2a00m0na001000c.html |title=Kyushu Electric bid to manipulate public opinion on reactor restart a colossal mistake |website=The Mainichi Daily News |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110708223518/http://mdn.mainichi.jp/perspectives/news/20110708p2a00m0na001000c.html |archivedate=2011-07-08 |accessdate=October 24, 2016}}</ref>
== History == Kyushu Electric Power was founded on May 1, 1951. The company began supplying electricity to [[Hiroshima]] in November 2005 - the first provider in Japan to supply energy outside its area.{{citation needed|date=October 2016}}
