'''Ramesh Agrawal''' is an [[India]]n social worker, internet café owner and grassroots environmentalist from [[Chhattisgarh]]. He was awarded the [[Goldman Environmental Prize]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.goldmanprize.org/recipient/ramesh-agrawal |title=Prize Recipient: Ramesh Agrawal, 2014 Asia |publisher=[[Goldman Environmental Prize]]|accessdate=6 June 2014}}</ref> in 2014 for his efforts in organizing protests against certain industrialization plans in the region, and in particular informing citizens about environmental and social consequences of projected large-scale [[coal mining]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.dnaindia.com/india/report-who-tried-to-kill-ramesh-agrawal-the-activist-and-winner-of-the-prestigious-goldman-environment-prize-1983875|title=Who tried to kill Ramesh Agrawal, the activist and winner of the prestigious Goldman Environment Prize?|date=2014-04-30|work=dna|access-date=2018-09-25|language=en-US}}</ref>

